label: Mexican Summer
description:
Taja Cheek's third L'Rain album is a mangled tapestry of psychedelic rock, R&B, radio pop, prog and folk references that's woven with distinctly unique threads. Brimming with sensually familiar earworms and devious, experimental touches, it's like hearing musical history reframed with rare literacy and spirit. Massive recommendation, whether yr into Joan Baez, TV On The Radio, serpentwithfeet or Moses Sumney.

label: Parallel Minds
description:
Ciel cycles thru atmospheric steppers and restless garage-techno swing on her debut album, proper

‘Homesick’ was forged in the wake of the C19 lockdown, when the artist hit a creative streak during days at her studio desk. The downtime afforded by the pandemic prompted Ciel to firm up her production ideas with strong influence from her research of traditional Chinese instrumentation which lends a spirit to the bare boned functionality of her rhythm tracks.
